<br>
<a href=http://www30.brinkster.com/djseng/SotO/default.asp>Scream of the Owl</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umistwolfeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MistwolfEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/7/02 7:00:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4084.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggested combo?</span><hr size=1> I'd do BP/FB when ure with the enchant.  Im assuming theres no one there to heal you, so the BP might be able to get you some HP's back.  When you need aggro, switch to FB/BP.<br>
<br>
For 10k, check out a Long Sword of Ethereal Energy [LSoEE]<br>
<br>
Its a nice offhand ratio weap for round 10k.  16/29 with like +15 dex (awsome for FB procs).  ITs got +5 magic damage so the weapon becomes 21/29 offhand which is pretty nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaylonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaylonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/7/02 11:06:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4084.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggested combo?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for advice.  Actually my core group is usually Me, Enchanter(53), and Druid(52) so i do have healer.  Also, I partner alot with the Druid and using the BP seems to work well to save her some mana. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=181233" TARGET="_Blank"><img
src="http://bellsouthpwp.net/R/a/RafaelSmith/Gaylon_Sig5.jpg"  border=0 alt="Inspect Gaylon"></A>
