<li><a href="http://pub89.ezboard.com/bmithanielmarr64528">Mithaniel Marr Darkside</a><li><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior">The Steel Warrior</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umistwolfeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MistwolfEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/7/02 12:34:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4084.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggested combo?</span><hr size=1> Werent you wielding two BP's before?  Guess you sold one and got a FB.  <br>
<br>
I think hes doing the small group duo or trio.  With a druid and chanter, I dont think theres much of an aggro problem.  Im assuming that you exp group with these people and they are there mostly to support you and kill things faster.  <br>
<br>
I duo/two box with a druid and Im going the 2 hander method instead.  Druid rarely gets hit because hes mostly there for support, damage shield, and heals.  So I'm using a Stone Bladed Axe of Dismay which has a 44/44 ratio.  For pure damage, this sucker is awsome.  Killing the mobs faster will mean less healing and less downtime.  I was weiding FB/LSoEE and it was good for aggro but that wasnt the issue.  For MAX damage output, I'd suggest looking into 2 handers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utalonfar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talonfar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/7/02 12:37:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4084.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.mtgcity.com/images/lotus.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggested combo?</span><hr size=1> Stone Bladed Axe of Dismay &gt; FB + LSoEE/BP<br>
<br>
44/44 will out taunt almost any 1hs combo pre NToV and Epic.  At least this has been my experience. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193604" target=new><font size=5 face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif" color=darkred>Keelz Neversleep</font></a><BR><font size=2 face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><I>
